## Application 
- Open the "**APP**" folder and then run the *assignment.exe* file, you will see an interface as follow: 

![Application interface](data:image/png;base64,)

## Features
- First, you need to fill in the start and destination location. You can also pick them from the map using the pickers. After using the picker for start location, the next picker is automatically triggered.
- Toggle map button: hide and show the map. 
- Toggle graph: show full graph with connected edges. The arrow indicates an 1-way while the rhombus indicates a 2-way edge. you can also tap on the path to see road names and their information. 

![Some basic features]()

- Tap buttons to see the paths on the map and it will show all paths taken on the scene. You can hover to each path to see their distances (or capacities):

![Some basic features]()

- You can also navigate between paths. Tap on paths to see road names (this is not activated in full paths view).

![Some basic features]()
